My Demands are as follows:<br>
50 Dwarfie Pickles<br>
AND ONE MILLION COPPER HAHAHAHA!!!<br>
<br>
If these demands are not met I will shave all of the hair off of her feet!!!  Then I will hand her over to the Clerics at the Spires of Innoruuk, they love halflings, the more sacrifices the better. <p><FONT COLOR="RED">
Srinn Hungry<BR>
Teir'Dal Warrior of Rallos-Zek<BR>
Rising Ogre Emire</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucatrintruesilverofwildfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Catrin Truesilver of Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/17/00 9:27:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BREAKING NEWS:  Thicket Murder Spree Continues</span><hr size=1> I am horrified at the dark turn this has taken for the young halfling; yet we may rejoice that she lives still, albiet in the hands of a dark Teir'Dal.<br>
<br>
While I was neither born nor raised in Rivervale, and, indeed hale from faraway Kelethin, I was touched by the beauty, peace and laughter that seemed to bubble out of Rivervale the very first time I saw it. Indeed, I have come to view Rivervale as a second home.<br>
<br>
While I cannot countenance paying in the coin of Dwarvish pickles, and am dubious indeed about paying ransom of any kind to one of the dark, I stand ready to assist the denizens of the Vale, with spell, lore, track, and blade!<br>
<br>
Whispered aside (in average Thieves Cant) to the Vale only: <br>
Aye, I speak the tongue; some know the tale of how a servant of Tunare came to speak it; suffice to say I am sworn as are all rogues -- err.. Gentlemen and Lady Privateers not to teach it to others. Now... perhaps it is the influence of Mumsley, perhaps I am beginning to think such as thee as I speak as one of you. If we promised a downpayment -- perhaps 10,000 copper in order to see her, and ensure that she is all right, and that no halfling would harm him... well, I am no halfling, and 10,000 copper would weigh a warrior down nicely! Tunare forgive me, but I would countenance a little duplicity without outright oathbreaking in order to save an innocent! I can also call upon my elven brothers and sisters to assist! <br>
<br>
..Catrin Truesilver,<br>
Druid of 40 seasons service to Tunare.<br>
